p:
Adolescents are a vulnerable group and they are experiencing a time of difficult transition (
 Swick et al., 2002; 
 Larsen and Luna, 2018; 
 Sturman and Moghaddam, 2011). The COVID-19 outbreak and lockdown may have multiple consequences on the lives of adolescents: chronic and acute stress, worry for their families, unexpected bereavements, sudden school break, and home confinement in many countries, increased time of access to the internet and social media, worry for the economic future of their family and country.
